#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an7.73"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.73:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.73:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an7.73:0.3"
msgid "73. Sunettasutta "
msgstr "73. About Sunetta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an7.73:1.1"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sunetto nāma satthā ahosi titthakaro kāmesu vītarāgo. "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, there was a Teacher called Sunetta. He was a religious founder and was free of sensual desire. "

msgctxt "an7.73:1.2"
msgid "Sunettassa kho pana, bhikkhave, satthuno anekāni sāvakasatāni ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "He had many hundreds of disciples. "

msgctxt "an7.73:1.3"
msgid "Sunetto satthā sāvakānaṃ brahmalokasahabyatāya dhammaṃ desesi. "
msgstr "He taught them the path to rebirth in the company of Brahmā. "

#. VAR: kho pana, bhikkhave → ye kho bhikkhave (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an7.73:1.4"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, sunettassa satthuno brahmalokasahabyatāya dhammaṃ desentassa cittāni nappasādesuṃ te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjiṃsu. "
msgstr "Those lacking confidence in Sunetta were—when their body broke up, after death—reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "an7.73:1.5"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, sunettassa satthuno brahmalokasahabyatāya dhammaṃ desentassa cittāni pasādesuṃ te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjiṃsu. "
msgstr "Those full of confidence in Sunetta were—when their body broke up, after death—reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.136, sc2
msgctxt "an7.73:2.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, mūgapakkho nāma satthā ahosi … pe … "
msgstr "Once upon a time there was a teacher called Mūgapakkha … "

msgctxt "an7.73:2.2"
msgid "aranemi nāma satthā ahosi … pe … "
msgstr "Aranemi … "

#. VAR: kuddālako → kuddālo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.73:2.3"
msgid "kuddālako nāma satthā ahosi … pe … "
msgstr "Kuddāla … "

msgctxt "an7.73:2.4"
msgid "hatthipālo nāma satthā ahosi … pe … "
msgstr "Hatthipāla … "

msgctxt "an7.73:2.5"
msgid "jotipālo nāma satthā ahosi … pe … "
msgstr "Jotipāla … "

msgctxt "an7.73:2.6"
msgid "arako nāma satthā ahosi titthakaro kāmesu vītarāgo. "
msgstr "Araka. He was a religious founder and was free of sensual desire. "

msgctxt "an7.73:2.7"
msgid "Arakassa kho pana, bhikkhave, satthuno anekāni sāvakasatāni ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "He had many hundreds of disciples. "

msgctxt "an7.73:2.8"
msgid "Arako nāma satthā sāvakānaṃ brahmalokasahabyatāya dhammaṃ desesi. "
msgstr "He taught them the way to rebirth in the company of Brahmā. "

msgctxt "an7.73:2.9"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, arakassa satthuno brahmalokasahabyatāya dhammaṃ desentassa cittāni nappasādesuṃ, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjiṃsu. "
msgstr "Those lacking confidence in Araka were—when their body broke up, after death—reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "an7.73:2.10"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, arakassa satthuno brahmalokasahabyatāya dhammaṃ desentassa cittāni pasādesuṃ, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjiṃsu. "
msgstr "Those full of confidence in Araka were—when their body broke up, after death—reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an7.73:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "an7.73:3.2"
msgid "yo ime satta satthāre titthakare kāmesu vītarāge anekasataparivāre sasāvakasaṅghe paduṭṭhacitto akkoseyya paribhāseyya, bahuṃ so apuññaṃ pasaveyyā”ti? "
msgstr "If someone with malicious intent were to abuse and insult these seven teachers with their hundreds of followers, would they not make much bad karma?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.73:3.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.73:3.4"
msgid "“Yo, bhikkhave, ime satta satthāre titthakare kāmesu vītarāge anekasataparivāre sasāvakasaṅghe paduṭṭhacitto akkoseyya paribhāseyya, bahuṃ so apuññaṃ pasaveyya. "
msgstr "“They would indeed. "

msgctxt "an7.73:3.5"
msgid "Yo ekaṃ diṭṭhisampannaṃ puggalaṃ paduṭṭhacitto akkosati paribhāsati, ayaṃ tato bahutaraṃ apuññaṃ pasavati. "
msgstr "But someone who abuses and insults a single person accomplished in view with malicious intent makes even more bad karma. "

msgctxt "an7.73:3.6"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an7.73:3.7"
msgid "Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ito bahiddhā evarūpiṃ khantiṃ vadāmi yathāmaṃ sabrahmacārīsu. "
msgstr "I say that any injury done by those outside of the Buddhist community does not compare with what is done to one’s own spiritual companions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an7.73:4.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "So you should train like this: "

#. VAR: na no sabrahmacārīsu → na tveva amhaṃ sabrahmacārīsu (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an7.73:4.2"
msgid "‘na no sabrahmacārīsu cittāni paduṭṭhāni bhavissantī’ti. "
msgstr "‘We will have no malicious intent for our spiritual companions.’ "

msgctxt "an7.73:4.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how you should train.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.73:4.4"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

